## Component Guidelines

### shadcn/ui Customization Rules

When installing shadcn components, always customize them:

1. Modify component variants to include brand-specific styles
2. Ensure all interactive elements use brand colors for focus states

### Tailark Marketing Component Rules

When adapting Tailark components:

1. Replace Tailark's default colors with brand semantic colors
2. Integrate shadcn/ui buttons and form elements
3. Add React Bits animations for scroll-triggered reveals
4. Maintain responsive design patterns

```tsx
// Example: Adapting a Tailark hero section
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { FadeIn } from "@/components/animations/fade-in"

export function HeroSection() {
  return (
    <section className="bg-background py-24">
      <FadeIn>
        <h1 className="text-primary text-5xl font-bold">
          Automate Your Business
        </h1>
        <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-4">
          Web scraping, workflow automation, and custom integrations.
        </p>
        <Button className="mt-8">Get Started</Button>
      </FadeIn>
    </section>
  )
}
```

### React Bits Animation Rules

Use React Bits for:
- Scroll-triggered fade-ins and slide-ins
- Staggered list animations
- Hover micro-interactions
- Page transitions

Animation principles:
- Keep animations subtle and professional (not playful)
- Duration: 200-400ms for micro-interactions, 400-800ms for reveals
- Easing: Use ease-out for entrances, ease-in-out for transitions
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

```tsx
// Create reusable animation wrappers
// src/components/animations/fade-in.tsx
"use client"

import { motion } from "framer-motion"

interface FadeInProps {
  children: React.ReactNode
  delay?: number
  direction?: "up" | "down" | "left" | "right"
}

export function FadeIn({ children, delay = 0, direction = "up" }: FadeInProps) {
  const directionOffset = {
    up: { y: 24 },
    down: { y: -24 },
    left: { x: 24 },
    right: { x: -24 },
  }

  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, ...directionOffset[direction] }}
      whileInView={{ opacity: 1, x: 0, y: 0 }}
      viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.5, delay, ease: "easeOut" }}
    >
      {children}
    </motion.div>
  )
}
```

### Icon Usage Rules

**Prefer AnimateIcons for:**
- Navigation icons
- Feature icons
- Interactive elements that benefit from animation

**Use Lucide for:**
- Static icons in text
- Small UI indicators
- When AnimateIcons doesn't have the needed icon

```tsx
