## Content & Copy Guidelines

### Voice & Tone

- **Professional:** We're experts, but not stuffy
- **Clear:** No jargon without explanation
- **Confident:** State capabilities directly
- **Helpful:** Focus on client outcomes, not our process

### Writing Style

- Use active voice
- Keep sentences concise
- Lead with benefits, follow with features
- Include specific outcomes when possible

```
❌ "Our automation solutions leverage cutting-edge technology..."
✅ "Automate repetitive tasks and save 10+ hours per week."

❌ "We provide web scraping services."  
✅ "Extract product data from 1,000+ websites automatically."
```

### Headlines

- Keep under 10 words
- Start with action verbs or outcomes
- Use sentence case (not Title Case)

---

## Accessibility Requirements

- All images must have alt text
- Interactive elements need visible focus states
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text)
- Support keyboard navigation
- Include skip links
- Use semantic HTML elements

```tsx
// Focus state example
<button className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:ring-offset-2">
  Click me
</button>
```

---

## Performance Guidelines

- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Implement lazy loading for below-fold content
- Keep initial JS bundle under 100KB
- Use server components by default
- Add loading states for async operations

